name: Patient's Age
definition: Age of the Patient.

name: Occupation
definition: Occupation of the Patient.

name: Confidentiality Constraint on Patient Data Description
definition: Special indication to the modality operator about confidentiality of patient information (e.g., that he should not use the patients name where other patients are present).

name: Patient's Birth Date
definition: Date of birth of the named patient.

name: Patient's Birth Time
definition: Time of birth of the named patient.

name: Patient's Sex
definition: Sex of the named patient.
comments: Enumerated Values: M - male;  F - female; O - other

name: Quality Control Subject
definition: Indicates whether or not the subject is a quality control phantom.
comments:
Enumerated values: YES, NO. 

If this Attribute is absent, then the subject may or may not be a phantom.
This attribute describes a characteristic of the Imaging Subject. 
It is distinct from Quality Control Image (0028,0300) in the General Image Module, which is used to describe an image acquired.

name: Patient's Insurance Plan Code Sequence
definition: A sequence that conveys the patient's insurance plan. Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

name: Patient's Primary Language Code Sequence
definition: The languages that can be used to communicate with the patient.
comments: Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence. The sequence items are ordered by preference (most preferred language to least preferred language). Baseline CID 5000 “Languages”.

name: Patient's Primary Language Modifier Code Sequence
definition: A modifier for a Patient's Primary Language. Can be used to specify a national language variant.
comments: Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence. Baseline CID 5001 “Countries”.

name: Patient's Size
definition: Patient's height or length in meters.

name: Patient's Weight
definition: Weight of the patient in kilograms.

name: Patient's Size Code Sequence
definition: Patient's size category code.

name: Patient's Address
definition: Legal address of the named patient.

name: Military Rank
definition: Military rank of patient.

name: Branch of Service
definition: Branch of the military. The country allegiance may also be included (e.g., U.S. Army).

name: Country of Residence
definition: Country in which patient currently resides.

name: Region of Residence
definition: Region within patient's country of residence.

name: Patient's Telephone Numbers
definition: Telephone numbers at which the patient can be reached.

name: Patient's Telecom Information
definition: The patient's personal telecommunication contact information, including telephone, email, or other telecom addresses.
comments:
Note: 
1. This attribute may have internal format or structure in accordance with local agreement or profile.
2. It is recommended that this attribute be treated as equivalent to HL7v2 fields PID-13 and PID-14, or PID-40 (v2.7 and later), and be formatted in accordance with the HL7v2 XTN data type (without escapes for HL7 message structure reserved characters).

name: Ethnic Group
definition: Ethnic group or race of patient.

name: Patient's Religious Preference
definition: The religious preference of the patient.

name: Patient Comments
definition: User-defined comments about the patient.

name: Responsible Person
definition: Name of person with medical decision making authority for the patient.

name: Responsible Person Role
definition: Relationship of Responsible Person to the patient.
comments: See Section C.7.1.1.1.2 for Defined Terms.

name: Responsible Organization
definition: Name of organization with medical decision making authority for the patient.

name: Patient Species Description
definition: The species of the patient.

name: Patient Species Code Sequence
definition: The species of the patient.

name: Patient Breed Description
definition: The breed of the patient.

name: Patient Breed Code Sequence
definition: The breed of the patient.

name: Breed Registration Sequence
definition: Information identifying an animal within a breed registry.

name: Breed Registration Number
definition: Identification number of a veterinary patient within the registry.

name: Breed Registry Code Sequence
definition: Identification of the organization with which an animal is registered.
